# [AIPREF](../wg/aipref.html)

## Summary

The AIPREF working group held a virtual interim meeting on June 9, 2026, to review the latest updates to `draft-ietf-aipref-vocab` (version 06), address outstanding issues from the Toronto interim, and plan the path forward for the upcoming IETF meeting in Vienna. 

The primary focus of the meeting was to address lack of convergence on key parts of the draft. Key discussions centered on the public interest exceptions and conformance safeguards in Section 3.2, refining the definitions for training (Section 4.1) and search (Section 4.2), and exploring a potential new category for inference-time/grounding usage (Issue 172) in light of recent regulatory developments.

The presentation slides for the session can be found here:
* [Chair Slides](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/interim-2026-aipref-09/materials/slides-interim-2026-aipref-09-sessa-chair-slides-00)

